<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>DDB0292</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Campaign to Protect Rural England – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The Campaign to Protect Rural England (CPRE) welcomes the opportunity to submit comments on the draft Deregulation Bill. CPRE exists to promote the beauty, tranquillity and diversity of rural England by encouraging the sustainable use of land and other natural resources in town and country. As a charity with a branch in every English county, over 200 district groups, and with more than 2,000 parish council members, we have considerable local and national expertise concerning planning policy.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">CPRE’s comments on the draft Bill focus on the provisions that affect the environment. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We support the submission by the Ramblers on the </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Use of Land </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">clauses 12-18 and Schedule 6 welcoming the inclusion of the rights of way clauses in the draft Deregulation Bill.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Specific comments on the draft Bill</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Clause 44</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Repeal of duty to prepare sustainable community strategy</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">While we support the intentions of the Government’s localism agenda we are concerned about the proposal to remove the requirement on local authorities to work with the communities in their area to develop a Sustainable Community Strategy. These strategies </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">set the overall direction and long-term vision for improving the economic, social and environmental well-being of a local area. We are concerned that due to limited resources, and the Government’s current focus on economic growth, removing the requirement for these strategies to be developed will result in less consideration being given to social and environmental well-being.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We urge the Committee to give consideration to whether this clause will result in social and environmental issues being </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">deprioritised</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> at the local level.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Clause 51</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Orders </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">disapplying</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> legislation no longer of practical use (1) A Minister of the Crown may by order provide for legislation to cease to apply if the Minister considers that it is no longer of practical use. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">CPRE suggests that the clause should be revised so that it states ‘if the Minister </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">reasonably</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> considers</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">..’</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">.  This is a very broad power and adding this one word would ensure the Minister is required to present an objective justification to cease to apply legislation. We are concerned that, without this change, the power could be used capriciously.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Schedule 15 </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Removal of consultation requirements</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">CPRE believes that Natural England should continue to be consulted on issues that affect National Parks or Areas of Outstanding Natural Beauty. We therefore do not support clauses 7 (grants reclaiming or improving derelict land), 12 (National Park grant) or 16 (grants to AONB Conservation Boards). Natural England has valuable experience and expertise in this area and should play vital role in advising the Government on environmental and land use matters, particularly in relation to designated landscapes. CPRE believes that the Government should be required to access </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">suchexpert</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> advice in </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">order to inform its decisions. We therefore do not support clause 13 which removes the requirement for the Minister to ‘consult bodies whose statutory functions include giving advice to Ministers relating to environmental conservation’.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">In conclusion, CPRE would make a more general point regarding the duty to promote economic growth.  While we recognise the need for and the benefits of growth, it should be sustainable and not pursued ‘at any cost’.  This should help ensure both long term viability of economic development and that impacts on communities and the environment are taken into account and managed. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>